Anthrax, Slovakia
-----------------
Information received on (and dated) 13 Nov 2012 from Dr Jozef Bires, director & chief veterinary officer, State Veterinary and Food Administration, Ministry of Agriculture, Bratislava, Slovakia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 5 Nov 2012
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 8 Nov 2012
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: August 2010
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: Staskovce, Stropkov, Presov
Date of start of the outbreak: 5 Nov 2012
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 153 / 3 / 3 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Cattle on pasture:
- under 6 months: 24 animals
- from 6 to 24 months: 26 animals
- over 24 months: 100 animals

Outbreak 2: Staskovce, Stropkov, Presov
Date of start of the outbreak: 10 Nov 2012
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 124 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: cattle on farm:
- from 6 to 24 months: 34 animals
- over 24 months: 89 animals

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 277 / 4 / 4 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 1.44 per cent / 1.44 per cent / 100 per cent / 1.44 per cent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: probably former burial of animals

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no vaccination; treatment of affected animals (antibiotics)
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
State Veterinary Institute, Zvolen (National laboratory) / Cattle / real-time PCR / 08 Nov 2012 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [available at the source URL above.]

